Why FastAPI sits in front of Kafka
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Splunk does NOT speak Kafka natively                   │
│                                                         │
│  Splunk webhook = simple HTTP POST                      │
│  Kafka = binary protocol, needs producer client        │
│                                                         │
│  FastAPI bridges the two:                              │
│  HTTP world ──► FastAPI ──► Kafka world                │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

FastAPI responsibilities in this path:

Step	What FastAPI Does
Receive	Accept HTTP POST from Splunk
Authenticate	Validate API token/secret
Acknowledge	Return HTTP 200 immediately to Splunk
Validate	Check payload has required fields
Produce	Write validated event to Kafka topic
Error	Malformed payload → reject 400, log it
Why return 200 immediately (before Kafka write):

Splunk has a short webhook timeout window.
If your processing is slow, Splunk marks it failed
and may retry — causing duplicates.

Pattern:
1. Receive POST
2. Return 200 ACK  ← do this FAST
3. Then write to Kafka async

